# CODEOWNERS — routes founder-only paths to review (see CORRECTION below
# for its real enforcement status today)
#
# GitHub's CODEOWNERS mechanism only understands real GitHub accounts, not
# the 11 Claude Code agent personas (they have no GitHub identity of their
# own -- see .claude/agents/README.md). So this file is scoped narrowly and
# deliberately: it only routes the paths that AUTONOMY.md marks
# `founder-only` (money, legal, security-toggle, and any edit to the
# governance rules themselves) to the founder's own account.
#
# CORRECTION (2026-07-16, Security Lead review, FQ-78): this file's header
# originally claimed these paths get "a REAL, GitHub-enforced human-review
# gate that cannot be bypassed by a self-merge." That is NOT true as this
# repo's branch protection stands today -- GitHub only enforces CODEOWNERS
# when `require_code_owner_reviews` is on (`branches/main/protection`
# confirms it is currently `false`; `required_approving_review_count` is
# also `0`, set that way in DECISIONS.md 2026-06-21 because self-approval
# is structurally impossible in this single-account repo). As shipped, this
# file provides ADVISORY routing and visibility (who a founder-only-path PR
# should be reviewed by) -- not a blocking gate. Flipping
# `require_code_owner_reviews` on would be a separate, founder-only future
# decision, and it is not a trivial flip: this repo's own account
# (@admin-nutshell) is both the sole founder-account owner AND every PR
# author, and GitHub forbids self-approval -- turning enforcement on today
# would deadlock every founder-only-path PR shut, not protect it. That
# problem needs its own design (e.g. a second reviewing identity) before
# enforcement is viable; not attempted in this PR.
#
# Everything else in this repo is deliberately NOT listed here. Specialist
# review (Security Lead on a migration, Evals Lead on a prompt change, etc.)
# is a separate, agent-driven discipline recorded in the per-PR sign-off
# record (see docs/workflows/ and CONSTITUTION.md's review flow) -- it is
# not, and cannot be, enforced through this GitHub-native mechanism without
# a dedicated bot identity per role, which does not exist yet.

# Governance rules themselves -- always founder-only per AUTONOMY.md
.claude/team/AUTONOMY.md            @admin-nutshell
.claude/team/CONSTITUTION.md        @admin-nutshell
.coderabbit.yaml                    @admin-nutshell
/CLAUDE.md                          @admin-nutshell
/.github/CODEOWNERS                 @admin-nutshell

# Database migrations and RLS -- irreversible-by-nature, security-sensitive,
# and already founder-executed in practice (service_role migrations-only,
# CLAUDE.md non-negotiable #3) -- this just makes that existing practice a
# real, enforced GitHub gate instead of a documented convention.
/supabase/migrations/**             @admin-nutshell

# NOTE: branch-protection/enforce_admins toggling (AUTONOMY.md's
# branch-protection-toggle category) is an API-level action against GitHub's
# repo settings, not a file in this repo -- there is no path to route here.
# That category is enforced by the standing rule in AUTONOMY.md and by never
# using `gh pr merge --admin` or the enforce_admins toggle without the
# founder's direct, in-the-moment words (see project memory on this exact
# point).
